    text: "\n\nThe business environment is the set of conditions that affect how a business operates. These conditions can include economic, political, social, technological, legal, and environmental factors. Economic factors include interest rates, inflation, and exchange rates. Political factors include government policies, regulations, and taxes. Social factors include consumer trends, population growth, and cultural values. Technological factors include advances in technology, the availability of new products, and the speed of communication. Legal factors include laws and regulations that affect how businesses operate. Environmental factors include climate change, natural disasters, and resource availability. All of these factors can have a significant impact on how a business operates and its success.",
    category: ["MANAGMENT", "MARKETING", "FINANCE", "HOSPITIALITY"],
