    indicator: "Evaluate vendor performance (OP:162) ",
    text: "\n\nEvaluating vendor performance is an important part of managing a business. It involves assessing the quality of the products or services provided by a vendor, as well as the timeliness and cost of the vendor's delivery. It is important to evaluate vendor performance in order to ensure that the vendor is meeting the expectations of the business and providing the best value for money. This evaluation should be done on a regular basis in order to ensure that the vendor is meeting the standards set by the business.",
