    area: "Instructional Area: Business Law ",
    indicator: "Explain the nature of a compliance program (BL:162) ",
    text: "\n\nA compliance program is a set of policies and procedures designed to ensure that an organization is adhering to applicable laws and regulations. It is a comprehensive system that includes training, monitoring, and enforcement of rules and regulations. The program is designed to ensure that the organization is compliant with all relevant laws and regulations, and that any violations are addressed in a timely manner. Compliance programs are essential for organizations to protect themselves from legal and financial risks.",
