    indicator: "Explain the use of product placement (PR:323) ",
    text: "\n\nProduct placement is a form of advertising where a company pays to have its product featured in a movie, TV show, or other media. This type of advertising is used to create brand awareness and increase sales. Product placement can be subtle or overt, and it can be used to target specific audiences. For example, a company may pay to have its product featured in a movie that appeals to a certain demographic. Product placement can also be used to create a positive association between the product and the movie or TV show.",
