      "Compute key banking calculations (e.g., interest, annual percentage rate, exchange rates, etc.)(FI:544) ",
    text: "\n\nCompute key banking calculations refers to the ability to calculate various financial metrics related to banking. This includes interest, annual percentage rate (APR), exchange rates, and other calculations related to banking. Interest is the cost of borrowing money, and is usually expressed as a percentage of the amount borrowed. APR is the annual cost of a loan, including interest and other fees, expressed as a percentage. Exchange rates are the rate at which one currency can be exchanged for another. These calculations are important for banks to understand the financial implications of their decisions.",
