    text: "\n\nAnticipating unspoken customer needs means proactively looking for ways to meet customer needs that they may not have even realized they had. This could include offering additional services or products that the customer may not have known were available, or suggesting solutions to problems that the customer may not have been aware of. It is important to be proactive in anticipating customer needs in order to provide the best customer service possible.",
