    area: "Instructional Area: Customer Relations ",
    indicator: "Resolve reservation issues (CR:061) ",
    text: "\n\nReservation issues refer to any issues that arise when a customer attempts to make a reservation. This could include problems with the reservation system, incorrect information being entered, or any other issue that prevents the customer from successfully making a reservation. To resolve these issues, customer service representatives should first listen to the customer's concerns and attempt to identify the source of the problem. Once the source of the issue is identified, the customer service representative should work with the customer to find a solution that meets their needs. This could include offering alternative solutions, providing additional information, or helping the customer to make a new reservation.",
    category: ["HOSPITIALITY"],
