    area: "Instructional Area: Marketing ",
    indicator:
      "Identify factors that influence guest experiences throughout the guest life cycle (MK:027) ",
    text: "\n\nThe guest life cycle is the journey that a guest takes from the moment they become aware of a business to the moment they become a loyal customer. Factors that influence guest experiences throughout the guest life cycle include the quality of the product or service, the customer service, the marketing and advertising, the pricing, and the overall atmosphere of the business. Additionally, the guest's personal preferences, such as their budget, lifestyle, and interests, can also influence their experience. All of these factors can have a positive or negative impact on the guest's experience, and it is important for businesses to be aware of them in order to create a positive and memorable experience for their guests.",
