    area: "Instructional Area: Operations ",
    indicator: "Describe pest control strategies (OP:562) ",
    text: "\n\nPest control strategies refer to the methods used to reduce or eliminate the presence of pests in a given area. These strategies can include physical, chemical, biological, and cultural methods. Physical methods include trapping, fencing, and exclusion. Chemical methods involve the use of insecticides, herbicides, and other chemicals to kill or repel pests. Biological methods involve the use of natural predators, parasites, and pathogens to control pest populations. Cultural methods involve changing the environment to make it less hospitable to pests, such as removing food sources and providing habitat for natural predators.",
