    area: "Instructional Area: Professional Development ",
    indicator:
      "Discuss the role of destination management organizations (DMOs) (PD:414) ",
    text: "\n\nDestination Management Organizations (DMOs) are organizations that are responsible for the development, promotion, and management of a destination. DMOs are typically funded by local governments and other stakeholders, and are responsible for the overall success of a destination. DMOs are responsible for developing and implementing strategies to attract visitors, increase tourism, and improve the overall experience of visitors. They also work to ensure that the destination is well-maintained and that the local economy is supported. DMOs are also responsible for creating and managing events, festivals, and other activities to attract visitors and promote the destination. Additionally, DMOs are responsible for developing and managing marketing campaigns to promote the destination and attract visitors.",
