    area: "Instructional Area: Customer Relations ",
    indicator: "Explain management's role in customer relations (CR:008) ",
    text: "\n\nManagement plays an important role in customer relations. They are responsible for setting the tone and expectations for customer service, as well as ensuring that customer service staff are properly trained and equipped to handle customer inquiries and complaints. Management should also be actively involved in customer feedback and surveys to ensure that customer needs and expectations are being met. Additionally, management should be available to provide guidance and support to customer service staff when needed. Ultimately, management's role in customer relations is to ensure that customers are satisfied with their experience and that their needs are being met.",
    category: ["ENTREPRENEUR"],
